  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Toilets Reduce Absentees for 200 Kenyan Students</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Primary school age children in Western Kenya is on the rise and new schools are being built.  However, there are little to no funds to build toilets and hand-wash stations.  Consequently, children pass germs, get sick and miss school.  Chronic absenteeism reduces a child&apos;s academic performance and lessens their ability to achievement in later life.  Our project will build two six-stall toilets and multiple hand-wash stations to increase health, reduce absenteeism and increase academics.</narrative>
  </description>
